HEADWORD: Jerkinhead
<hw>Jer"kin*head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>The hipped part of a roof which is hipped only for a part of its
height, leaving a truncated gable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

